.SH NAME
acpi_device_sleep_wake \- execute _DSW (Device Sleep Wake) or (deprecated in ACPI 3.0) _PSW (Power State Wake)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" acpi_device_sleep_wake
.BI "(struct acpi_device *dev "  ","
.BI "int enable "  ","
.BI "int sleep_state "  ","
.BI "int dev_state "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
Device to handle.
.IP "enable" 12
0 - disable, 1 - enable the wake capabilities of the device.
.IP "sleep_state" 12
Target sleep state of the system.
.IP "dev_state" 12
Target power state of the device.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Execute _DSW (Device Sleep Wake) or (deprecated in ACPI 3.0) _PSW (Power
State Wake) for the device, if present.  On failure reset the device's
wakeup.flags.valid flag.

RETURN VALUE:
0 if either _DSW or _PSW has been successfully executed
0 if neither _DSW nor _PSW has been found
-ENODEV if the execution of either _DSW or _PSW has failed
